<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-08-07T00:24:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-08-07T00:24:00-05:00" n="855" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d855">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">311.6124/74: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Commissioner at Riga</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Young</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-08-07T07:00:00+01:36"><hi rend="italic">August 7,
                                        1920—7 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 11:21
                            a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>96. Esthonian Minister of Foreign Affairs informs me that despite
                            repeated requests no reply has been received from Moscow regarding
                            deportees.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Young</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>